NEW DELHI, Dec. 5 (Xinhua) -- At least six people were killed and many injured in an incident of firing in India's northeastern state of Nagaland, confirmed the state's Chief Minister Neiphiu Rio on Sunday. The incident took place late Saturday night in the state's Mon district, and the death toll is feared to rise, said media reports. "The unfortunate incident leading to killing of civilians at Oting, Mon district is highly condemnable. Condolences to the bereaved families and speedy recovery of those injured," tweeted the chief minister. He said high-level Special Investigation Team (SIT) will carry investigation and justice will be delivered as per the law. Enditem